1
00:00:01,034 --> 00:00:02,369
Neferpitou: It’s neferpitou.

2
00:00:02,402 --> 00:00:04,037
- Rammot: Huh?
- Peggy: Eh?

3
00:00:04,071 --> 00:00:06,974
Neferpitou: That is the name
the queen bestowed upon me.

4
00:00:07,007 --> 00:00:10,978
From now on,
you can call me neferpitou.

5
00:00:11,011 --> 00:00:11,778
♪

6
00:00:11,812 --> 00:00:14,014
( Singing in Japanese )

7
00:00:55,522 --> 00:00:57,524
♪

8
00:01:04,331 --> 00:01:07,201
Peggy: Attention,
squadron leaders and officers.

9
00:01:07,234 --> 00:01:10,471
Attention, squadron leaders
and officers.

10
00:01:10,504 --> 00:01:12,373
Commander neferpitou
will be holding

11
00:01:12,406 --> 00:01:14,208
a conferment ceremony
in hall one,

12
00:01:14,241 --> 00:01:18,045
and of course
you are all invited.

13
00:01:18,078 --> 00:01:19,446
( Rammot chuckles )

14
00:01:19,479 --> 00:01:21,047
( Knuckles crack )

15
00:01:21,081 --> 00:01:24,217
Peggy: A brief moment
of suffering, and in exchange,

16
00:01:24,251 --> 00:01:27,688
you will be rewarded with power
beyond your wildest dreams.

17
00:01:27,721 --> 00:01:29,489
All we ask in return

18
00:01:29,523 --> 00:01:33,293
is that you use this power
in service of the queen.

19
00:01:33,327 --> 00:01:35,329
♪

20
00:01:42,636 --> 00:01:45,305
Kite: They’re still moving
in a straight line,

21
00:01:45,339 --> 00:01:48,509
and that can only mean
that the chimera ant nest

22
00:01:48,542 --> 00:01:50,310
is almost certainly up ahead.

23
00:01:50,344 --> 00:01:52,646
Killua: Man, that’s amazing.

24
00:01:52,679 --> 00:01:56,416
He tracked ’em this whole time
and never lost them once.

25
00:01:56,450 --> 00:02:00,387
Gon: He said that his en
covers a radius of 45 meters.

26
00:02:00,420 --> 00:02:03,390
Killua: I’ve heard that
the ones called nen masters

27
00:02:03,423 --> 00:02:05,825
can handle around 50 meters.

28
00:02:05,859 --> 00:02:08,729
I’m guessing that kite’s
nearly there.

29
00:02:08,762 --> 00:02:11,732
Actually, he’s kept it up
for a whole night,

30
00:02:11,765 --> 00:02:13,400
so he’s probably stronger.

31
00:02:15,469 --> 00:02:17,604
Gon: Stronger
than a master, huh?

32
00:02:17,638 --> 00:02:20,608
♪

33
00:02:20,641 --> 00:02:23,577
He must be the real deal,
I guess.

34
00:02:23,610 --> 00:02:26,480
Killua: Yeah.
He’s the first pro we’ve met,

35
00:02:26,513 --> 00:02:28,148
well, at least like this.

36
00:02:28,182 --> 00:02:29,450
( No audible dialogue )

37
00:02:29,483 --> 00:02:33,654
I mean, tsezguerra was
definitely a pro hunter,

38
00:02:33,687 --> 00:02:37,324
but we really only knew him
as another player in a game.

39
00:02:37,357 --> 00:02:41,828
And bisky was an incredible
hunter, but to us...

40
00:02:41,862 --> 00:02:44,732
Gon: Yeah.
She was our nen master.

41
00:02:44,765 --> 00:02:46,367
Killua: And then
there was the first person

42
00:02:46,400 --> 00:02:47,668
to teach us about nen...

43
00:02:47,701 --> 00:02:51,538
Gon: Master wing,
our nen master and savior.

44
00:02:52,706 --> 00:02:55,509
Killua: And now
that I think about it,

45
00:02:55,542 --> 00:02:59,613
we always meet people
when we need them the most.

46
00:02:59,646 --> 00:03:02,549
It’s them,
all these people we’ve met,

47
00:03:02,583 --> 00:03:04,218
who have made us stronger.

48
00:03:04,251 --> 00:03:06,386
Gon: I guess razor counts,
too, huh?

49
00:03:06,420 --> 00:03:07,421
Killua: Yeah.

50
00:03:08,856 --> 00:03:10,591
It’s pretty obvious to me

51
00:03:10,624 --> 00:03:13,760
that ging really did create
"greed island" to train you,

52
00:03:13,794 --> 00:03:16,463
and then once you
finished beating the game,

53
00:03:16,497 --> 00:03:18,165
he led you to kite.

54
00:03:18,198 --> 00:03:20,367
Gon: Yeah!

55
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:22,769
♪

56
00:03:32,613 --> 00:03:35,182
Killua: I don’t know
if ging could have predicted

57
00:03:35,215 --> 00:03:38,685
what was gonna happen
when we met kite, but still...

58
00:03:41,755 --> 00:03:43,423
Kite had already
earned his respect,

59
00:03:43,457 --> 00:03:48,228
so he had to have known
that you would like him, too,

60
00:03:48,262 --> 00:03:51,499
and he definitely knew
you’d follow him.

61
00:03:51,532 --> 00:03:53,234
That much, i’m sure of.

62
00:03:53,267 --> 00:03:55,770
Gon: If he wants us
to travel with kite,

63
00:03:55,802 --> 00:03:57,871
then that means
he’ll make us stronger.

64
00:03:57,905 --> 00:03:59,540
Killua: You might be right,

65
00:03:59,573 --> 00:04:01,775
but this is a pretty brutal
place for training.

66
00:04:01,808 --> 00:04:03,843
Kite: And that is
exactly the reason

67
00:04:03,877 --> 00:04:06,880
why I keep asking you
if your resolve is firm.

68
00:04:06,914 --> 00:04:08,482
( Both gasp )

69
00:04:10,517 --> 00:04:13,653
Kite: I agree that,
like you mentioned,

70
00:04:13,687 --> 00:04:16,857
ging probably did have
certain expectations

71
00:04:16,890 --> 00:04:19,526
when he sent you here
to meet with me.

72
00:04:19,560 --> 00:04:22,396
That being said,
I have no intention

73
00:04:22,429 --> 00:04:24,965
of training the two of you
during this journey.

74
00:04:24,998 --> 00:04:27,434
We just don’t have
that kind of time.

75
00:04:27,467 --> 00:04:29,436
♪

76
00:04:29,469 --> 00:04:31,404
I only brought you along,

77
00:04:31,438 --> 00:04:33,874
because I thought
you might be useful.

78
00:04:33,907 --> 00:04:37,577
From here on, it all comes down
to your resolve.

79
00:04:37,611 --> 00:04:39,580
If it’s strong,

80
00:04:39,613 --> 00:04:43,250
you’ll develop your nen
and improve through combat.

81
00:04:43,283 --> 00:04:46,620
If it’s weak, the ants
will eat you, and you will die.

82
00:04:46,653 --> 00:04:48,021
( Both grunt )

83
00:04:48,055 --> 00:04:51,292
Kite: But that’s not
a luxury we can afford.

84
00:04:51,325 --> 00:04:54,061
We’re professional hunters,
after all,

85
00:04:54,094 --> 00:04:55,862
and as you’re aware,

86
00:04:55,896 --> 00:04:58,866
those who call themselves
hunters must get their prey.

87
00:04:58,899 --> 00:05:00,300
( Both gasp )

88
00:05:00,334 --> 00:05:02,403
Kite: For those
of our profession,

89
00:05:02,436 --> 00:05:03,971
that’s the first commandment.

90
00:05:04,004 --> 00:05:07,708
We stay on the hunt,
no matter what.

91
00:05:07,741 --> 00:05:11,945
A hunt involves both
the hunter and the hunted.

92
00:05:11,979 --> 00:05:14,515
It’s a battle of resolve.

93
00:05:14,548 --> 00:05:18,485
Emerging victorious
from a battle of resolve

94
00:05:18,519 --> 00:05:20,721
is what makes a hunt successful.

95
00:05:20,754 --> 00:05:24,658
The loser must follow
the winner’s rules and customs,

96
00:05:24,691 --> 00:05:26,760
and this often means
the loser’s death.

97
00:05:26,793 --> 00:05:28,762
Gon: Yeah. Okay.

98
00:05:28,795 --> 00:05:32,632
Kite: If that result
isn’t desirable, then win.

99
00:05:32,666 --> 00:05:35,035
Improving your nen
is important, sure,

100
00:05:35,068 --> 00:05:37,037
but to be a successful hunter,

101
00:05:37,070 --> 00:05:41,374
you must understand your enemy
as well as yourself.

102
00:05:41,408 --> 00:05:44,611
Gon: Wait. I get it!
That must be why you hit me

103
00:05:44,645 --> 00:05:46,947
when I met you
a long time ago, right?

104
00:05:46,980 --> 00:05:49,816
♪

105
00:05:52,586 --> 00:05:54,655
Kite: You imbecile!
Don’t you know better

106
00:05:54,688 --> 00:05:57,591
than to enter a snakebeech
forest this time of year?!

107
00:05:57,624 --> 00:05:59,893
- ( Gon gasps )
- Kite: See that?

108
00:05:59,927 --> 00:06:03,030
It’s the territorial Mark of
a foxbear when she’s with a cub!

109
00:06:03,063 --> 00:06:05,933
If you see that Mark,
then you stay away!

110
00:06:05,966 --> 00:06:08,469
Even the animals know that much!

111
00:06:08,502 --> 00:06:10,738
( Gon gasps )

112
00:06:10,771 --> 00:06:14,441
That was the rule of the forest.
It was, wasn’t it?

113
00:06:16,476 --> 00:06:20,747
You were teaching me the rules
in ging’s place.

114
00:06:27,387 --> 00:06:28,755
( Kite gasps )

115
00:06:28,789 --> 00:06:29,990
( Both gasp )

116
00:06:30,023 --> 00:06:31,558
Kite: Oh, that’s right.

117
00:06:31,592 --> 00:06:33,461
I just remembered.

118
00:06:37,431 --> 00:06:39,433
Gon: It’s a hunter’s license.

119
00:06:39,466 --> 00:06:40,600
Killua: But whose?

120
00:06:40,634 --> 00:06:42,402
Kite: It’s ging’s.

121
00:06:42,436 --> 00:06:44,605
Gon: Huh? It’s ging’s?

122
00:06:44,638 --> 00:06:47,541
Kite: Just think back
to my final test.

123
00:06:47,574 --> 00:06:49,009
Remember what it was?

124
00:06:49,042 --> 00:06:52,812
Gon: Mm. You told me
you had to go find ging.

125
00:06:52,846 --> 00:06:55,415
Kite: Well,
before the test even began,

126
00:06:55,449 --> 00:06:57,618
ging handed his license to me.

127
00:06:57,651 --> 00:07:02,356
He told me I was supposed
to use it to find him someday.

128
00:07:02,389 --> 00:07:04,024
♪

129
00:07:04,057 --> 00:07:07,894
I always planned
to return it to him once I did.

130
00:07:07,928 --> 00:07:10,397
Gon: Wait.
He wouldn’t take it back?

131
00:07:10,430 --> 00:07:14,501
Kite: No. I’d actually
forgotten I had it.

132
00:07:14,535 --> 00:07:15,503
( Both groan )

133
00:07:15,536 --> 00:07:17,972
Kite: Gon, you said you were

134
00:07:18,005 --> 00:07:20,708
gonna find ging on your own,
didn’t you?

135
00:07:20,741 --> 00:07:21,709
Gon: Uh...

136
00:07:21,742 --> 00:07:23,510
( Grunts )

137
00:07:23,544 --> 00:07:26,147
Kite: Then you have to do
what you said you would.

138
00:07:26,180 --> 00:07:27,682
And if you don’t mind,

139
00:07:27,714 --> 00:07:30,383
you think you could
return that to him for me?

140
00:07:30,417 --> 00:07:32,819
Gon: Sure,
but before I do that,

141
00:07:32,853 --> 00:07:34,788
I have to finish
this job with you

142
00:07:34,821 --> 00:07:36,923
and get a lot stronger
while we’re at it.

143
00:07:36,957 --> 00:07:41,562
Once i’m done, i’ll find ging
and give this back to him.

144
00:07:41,595 --> 00:07:44,064
You have my word.

145
00:07:44,097 --> 00:07:46,967
Kite: I’m counting on you.

146
00:07:47,968 --> 00:07:51,071
Well, time to get a move on.

147
00:07:51,104 --> 00:07:53,573
We don’t want to lose the trail.

148
00:07:57,644 --> 00:07:59,212
( Rammot yells )

149
00:08:00,581 --> 00:08:01,849
( Chimera ant crashes )

150
00:08:01,882 --> 00:08:03,117
Who’s next?

151
00:08:04,551 --> 00:08:06,853
Neferpitou:
Must be tough being ordinary,

152
00:08:06,887 --> 00:08:10,090
going through all this trouble
just to become powerful.

153
00:08:10,123 --> 00:08:11,124
( Rammot grunts )

154
00:08:12,492 --> 00:08:14,194
( Neferpitou giggles )

155
00:08:16,897 --> 00:08:18,999
Peggy, take care of the rest.

156
00:08:19,032 --> 00:08:20,467
Peggy: Where are you going?

157
00:08:20,501 --> 00:08:23,471
Neferpitou:
To check on something.

158
00:08:23,504 --> 00:08:26,507
I want to see
just how strong I am.

159
00:08:30,811 --> 00:08:32,479
Kite: A monster.

160
00:08:33,914 --> 00:08:35,015
What is this?

161
00:08:35,048 --> 00:08:36,716
I don’t believe it!

162
00:08:36,750 --> 00:08:38,719
Gon: What’s wrong, kite?

163
00:08:38,752 --> 00:08:40,487
Kite: Gon, killua, run.

164
00:08:40,521 --> 00:08:41,489
Both: Huh?

165
00:08:41,522 --> 00:08:43,057
Kite: I said go!

166
00:08:43,090 --> 00:08:45,092
Get out of here right now!

167
00:08:45,125 --> 00:08:47,127
♪

168
00:08:54,001 --> 00:08:56,136
Neferpitou: I found you.

169
00:08:59,940 --> 00:09:03,010
Kite: Get away!

170
00:09:07,714 --> 00:09:09,015
( Both gasp )

171
00:09:09,049 --> 00:09:11,051
( No audio )

172
00:09:14,188 --> 00:09:15,189
( Audio returns )

173
00:09:17,024 --> 00:09:18,993
( Gon shudders )

174
00:09:39,179 --> 00:09:42,949
( Yells )

175
00:09:42,983 --> 00:09:45,219
Kite: Idiot!

176
00:09:49,556 --> 00:09:51,224
Wise decision, killua.

177
00:09:52,693 --> 00:09:54,862
Now take gon,
and get out of here!

178
00:09:54,895 --> 00:09:56,864
( Killua gasps )

179
00:09:56,897 --> 00:09:58,899
( Wind blowing )

180
00:10:09,710 --> 00:10:12,112
( Crazy slots laughs )

181
00:10:12,145 --> 00:10:14,280
You’re in for it now.
You know that?

182
00:10:14,314 --> 00:10:16,917
Better hope for a good number.

183
00:10:16,950 --> 00:10:18,285
( Babbles )

184
00:10:18,318 --> 00:10:19,719
Three!

185
00:10:19,753 --> 00:10:22,289
Neferpitou: So you can
do that stuff, too?

186
00:10:47,014 --> 00:10:49,683
Killua: We were too complacent
and overconfident.

187
00:10:49,716 --> 00:10:52,519
♪

188
00:10:59,626 --> 00:11:03,497
We were both worth less
than a one-armed kite.

189
00:11:03,530 --> 00:11:06,600
That was his assessment.

190
00:11:06,633 --> 00:11:09,202
That’s the reality.

191
00:11:10,470 --> 00:11:12,105
If kite had been alone,

192
00:11:12,139 --> 00:11:15,042
this probably
wouldn’t have happened.

193
00:11:15,075 --> 00:11:17,044
( Gasps )

194
00:11:17,077 --> 00:11:20,681
Damn it. We were fools.

195
00:11:38,131 --> 00:11:40,100
Man: Hey...

196
00:11:45,138 --> 00:11:47,107
Is that...

197
00:11:47,140 --> 00:11:49,109
( Killua panting )

198
00:11:49,142 --> 00:11:51,144
♪

199
00:12:16,403 --> 00:12:18,505
( Cell phone beeping )

200
00:12:22,543 --> 00:12:24,545
( Line ringing )

201
00:12:27,514 --> 00:12:30,083
Spin: What?
You left kite behind?

202
00:12:30,117 --> 00:12:31,518
Why would you do that?!

203
00:12:31,552 --> 00:12:33,387
What happened out there?!

204
00:12:33,420 --> 00:12:35,122
You explain yourself
this instant!

205
00:12:35,155 --> 00:12:37,724
Hey, what the hell
do you think you’re doing?!

206
00:12:39,259 --> 00:12:41,394
Mon: Mm. I understand.

207
00:12:41,428 --> 00:12:43,363
Just wait there
for the time being.

208
00:12:43,397 --> 00:12:46,767
We’re all headed your way
right now, so it won’t be long.

209
00:12:48,135 --> 00:12:50,638
And we’re
bringing reinforcements.

210
00:12:55,409 --> 00:12:57,278
Killua: Huh?

211
00:13:04,251 --> 00:13:06,320
( Sighs )

212
00:13:27,207 --> 00:13:28,175
( Gasps )

213
00:13:28,208 --> 00:13:30,210
♪

214
00:13:34,314 --> 00:13:36,583
Chairman netero.

215
00:13:36,617 --> 00:13:38,586
Hunter: What the hell is this?

216
00:13:38,619 --> 00:13:40,154
They’re just kids.

217
00:13:40,187 --> 00:13:41,689
You got burned real bad,

218
00:13:41,722 --> 00:13:44,291
because you thought
this was gonna be a game.

219
00:13:44,324 --> 00:13:46,393
Just hurry on home
before it’s too late.

220
00:13:49,429 --> 00:13:51,398
Hunter #2: Stop it, Mr. Morel.

221
00:13:52,566 --> 00:13:54,334
That isn’t very nice.

222
00:13:54,368 --> 00:13:55,536
( Morel growls )

223
00:13:56,570 --> 00:13:58,338
Hunter #2: As you said yourself,

224
00:13:58,372 --> 00:13:59,540
they are only children.

225
00:14:01,909 --> 00:14:04,478
( Netero chuckles )

226
00:14:04,511 --> 00:14:07,681
You certainly seem to be
down in the dumps.

227
00:14:09,316 --> 00:14:11,885
So was your adversary
that formidable?

228
00:14:11,919 --> 00:14:13,888
( Killua gasps )

229
00:14:20,227 --> 00:14:22,896
One of them could use nen.

230
00:14:22,930 --> 00:14:25,533
Of all the aura
i’ve encountered,

231
00:14:25,566 --> 00:14:27,635
this one was the worst...

232
00:14:29,269 --> 00:14:32,372
Worse than my brother’s...

233
00:14:33,774 --> 00:14:36,243
Or hisoka’s.

234
00:14:39,680 --> 00:14:43,551
Now that i’ve learned nen
myself, I can tell.

235
00:14:45,252 --> 00:14:47,554
You guys are
unbelievably strong...

236
00:14:49,790 --> 00:14:53,260
And still, I don’t think
even you could take him.

237
00:14:59,733 --> 00:15:01,268
( Hunter #2 scoffs )

238
00:15:01,301 --> 00:15:03,837
People overrate things
that they can’t understand,

239
00:15:03,871 --> 00:15:07,441
and that is
a perfectly natural response.

240
00:15:07,474 --> 00:15:11,645
Unfortunately you’re in a state
of extreme panic right now.

241
00:15:11,678 --> 00:15:13,680
We’ll take it from here.

242
00:15:13,714 --> 00:15:17,251
You just go to bed
and get some rest.

243
00:15:17,284 --> 00:15:18,786
( Morel laughs )

244
00:15:18,819 --> 00:15:22,256
How was that just now
different from what I said?

245
00:15:22,289 --> 00:15:23,257
Come on, knov.

246
00:15:23,290 --> 00:15:25,659
( Knov scoffs )

247
00:15:25,692 --> 00:15:28,929
Morel: Look, kid,
the minute you start calculating

248
00:15:28,962 --> 00:15:31,331
the odds of winning
in nen combat,

249
00:15:31,365 --> 00:15:33,701
well, it just shows
you’re missing the whole point.

250
00:15:33,734 --> 00:15:35,936
In most cases,

251
00:15:35,969 --> 00:15:39,506
you don’t know what
your opponent’s abilities are,

252
00:15:39,540 --> 00:15:42,243
and when you’re
in a fight like that,

253
00:15:42,276 --> 00:15:43,911
even the slightest hesitation

254
00:15:43,944 --> 00:15:47,714
can be a matter
of life or death.

255
00:15:47,748 --> 00:15:51,986
All of a sudden, having more
or less aura than the other guy

256
00:15:52,019 --> 00:15:54,421
isn’t really much of an excuse.

257
00:15:54,454 --> 00:15:57,724
Plus, the battle can
turn quickly and at any time.

258
00:15:57,758 --> 00:16:01,262
That’s the essence
of nen combat.

259
00:16:01,295 --> 00:16:03,864
Still, no matter what,

260
00:16:03,897 --> 00:16:07,501
always fight like you know
you’re gonna win.

261
00:16:07,534 --> 00:16:11,705
That’s what it means to have
the spirit of a nen user.

262
00:16:11,738 --> 00:16:13,573
You were disqualified

263
00:16:13,607 --> 00:16:16,777
the second you got scared
of your opponent’s nen and ran.

264
00:16:16,810 --> 00:16:18,478
You’re worse than a loser.

265
00:16:18,512 --> 00:16:20,714
Knov: Morel, that’s enough.

266
00:16:21,915 --> 00:16:24,718
Netero: Is gon
sound asleep there?

267
00:16:24,751 --> 00:16:26,553
Killua: No, he’s not.

268
00:16:26,587 --> 00:16:30,324
He tried to attack,
so I used force to stop him,

269
00:16:31,625 --> 00:16:33,727
I didn’t have time to hold back,

270
00:16:33,760 --> 00:16:35,729
so I don’t know
when he’ll wake up.

271
00:16:35,762 --> 00:16:37,464
( Morel laughs )

272
00:16:37,497 --> 00:16:40,300
Sounds like the other kid’s
got a lot more of a future.

273
00:16:40,334 --> 00:16:41,569
Knov: Morel.

274
00:16:41,602 --> 00:16:44,405
Netero: It’s rather
difficult to believe

275
00:16:44,438 --> 00:16:47,841
that giant chimera ants
have taken to eating humans,

276
00:16:47,875 --> 00:16:49,844
yet it seems to be true,

277
00:16:49,877 --> 00:16:51,512
and therefore we must attempt

278
00:16:51,545 --> 00:16:53,680
to keep the casualties
to a minimum.

279
00:16:53,714 --> 00:16:56,684
If we send in fighters
who aren’t strong enough,

280
00:16:56,717 --> 00:16:59,053
we’re running the risk
of assimilation.

281
00:16:59,086 --> 00:17:01,088
Do you understand?

282
00:17:01,121 --> 00:17:02,956
Killua: Yeah.

283
00:17:08,929 --> 00:17:10,964
That’s why
there are only three,

284
00:17:10,998 --> 00:17:13,634
a select few.

285
00:17:14,801 --> 00:17:16,936
We’re not strong enough,

286
00:17:16,970 --> 00:17:19,673
not by a long shot.

287
00:17:26,046 --> 00:17:28,382
Netero: We have already
placed two assassins

288
00:17:28,415 --> 00:17:30,083
in the nearest city.

289
00:17:30,117 --> 00:17:31,685
( Killua gasps )

290
00:17:33,453 --> 00:17:36,856
Netero: Whether or not you want
to fight them is up to you.

291
00:17:36,890 --> 00:17:41,094
However, if you truly
want to live as a hunter,

292
00:17:41,128 --> 00:17:44,965
take them down,
and come find us.

293
00:17:48,569 --> 00:17:50,538
We don’t need just any help...

294
00:17:51,805 --> 00:17:53,907
Only the strong.

295
00:17:53,941 --> 00:17:55,976
♪

296
00:18:35,682 --> 00:18:37,417
Morel: You were disqualified

297
00:18:37,451 --> 00:18:41,789
the second you got scared
of your opponent’s nen and ran.

298
00:18:41,822 --> 00:18:44,158
You’re worse than a loser.

299
00:18:45,592 --> 00:18:48,862
Killua: I’m no longer qualified.

300
00:18:50,631 --> 00:18:53,167
- Gon: Killua.
- ( Killua gasps )

301
00:18:53,200 --> 00:18:55,803
Gon: Thanks a lot.

302
00:18:59,139 --> 00:19:00,807
( Killua shudders )

303
00:19:02,042 --> 00:19:05,746
"Thank you"?
Why would you say that?

304
00:19:05,779 --> 00:19:08,815
Gon: Well,
because you knocked me out.

305
00:19:08,849 --> 00:19:10,884
It was you, right?

306
00:19:10,918 --> 00:19:13,554
I mean, if i’d
lost control back there,

307
00:19:13,587 --> 00:19:15,756
I would have
gotten in the way...

308
00:19:18,091 --> 00:19:21,761
And if I had,
all three of us would have died.

309
00:19:21,795 --> 00:19:24,898
Killua: Maybe, but I just--

310
00:19:24,932 --> 00:19:27,168
I left kite back there to die.

311
00:19:27,201 --> 00:19:29,070
Gon: Kite is still alive.

312
00:19:29,102 --> 00:19:30,136
( Killua gasps )

313
00:19:30,170 --> 00:19:32,205
Gon: He would never be beaten,

314
00:19:32,239 --> 00:19:34,208
not by something like that.

315
00:19:35,809 --> 00:19:39,179
But he did get injured,

316
00:19:39,213 --> 00:19:41,916
and in his shape,
just trying to move

317
00:19:41,949 --> 00:19:45,820
is pretty hard on him,
so he’s hiding.

318
00:19:45,853 --> 00:19:48,222
He’s waiting for us
to come back.

319
00:19:51,258 --> 00:19:56,864
So now we get strong,
and we find him.

320
00:19:58,832 --> 00:20:00,967
We’re gonna go save kite.

321
00:20:01,001 --> 00:20:03,670
♪

322
00:20:06,673 --> 00:20:07,674
Killua: Gon...

323
00:20:12,546 --> 00:20:15,149
You’re light itself.

324
00:20:20,954 --> 00:20:23,623
Yeah. Yeah, you’re right.

325
00:20:25,792 --> 00:20:27,294
( Thinking )
Sometimes you’re so bright,

326
00:20:27,327 --> 00:20:29,296
I can’t even look at you.

327
00:20:31,798 --> 00:20:35,869
But still,
can I stay by your side?

328
00:20:40,274 --> 00:20:42,042
- Let’s go.
- ( Bird tweeting )

329
00:20:43,777 --> 00:20:45,612
We’ve gotta get stronger.

330
00:20:52,686 --> 00:20:54,688
♪

331
00:21:00,661 --> 00:21:03,564
Colt: Prepare a freezing chamber
in the fortress!

332
00:21:03,597 --> 00:21:07,301
Make it large enough to store
more than a hundred humans!

333
00:21:09,036 --> 00:21:13,607
Neferpitou: To ensure
that my collection doesn’t rot.

334
00:21:14,641 --> 00:21:16,209
Yup!

335
00:21:16,243 --> 00:21:22,983
I think i’m pretty strong
after all

336
00:21:25,052 --> 00:21:25,853
♪

337
00:21:25,886 --> 00:21:27,888
( Singing in Japanese )

